  "texts": [
    "Innovations in cooling technologies, such as microfluidic systems and phase-change materials, should be a focal point.",
    "Additionally, researchers should invest in modeling and simulation tools that accurately consider thermal effects in diverse environmental conditions.",
    "Engineers play a vital role in implementing effective cooling strategies tailored to specific environmental conditions.",
    "This includes the adoption of smart technologies, such as AI-driven tracking systems and dynamic shading devices, to optimize solar panel performance in realtime.",
    "Regular maintenance protocols, including cleaning to mitigate dust accumulation, and monitoring solar panel temperatures and performance, are crucial for early anomaly detection."
